caption: Literally my favorite place to get food in Brooklyn. The meatballs are from planet awesome. Chicken and two sides, best deal in town. Thank you Mr. Brancaccio!
If they ONLY sold the meatball sandwich this place would still be 🙏🏽🙏🏽🙏🏽 (go early, otherwise you might miss-out) - - Everything they make is QUALITY

*updated 3/24/21--the owner is so cantankerous that I'm going to upgrade to a 5-star just for keeping it real! No deli meats but authenticity in abundance! Just keep those menus posted! :) * Crabby server at counter. No substitutes and no deli meats. I love small biz but this guy was a turn off. He didn't even have menus posted so I couldn't know what was served
Chicken soup and cheese danish is always 🔥🔥🔥🔥

Brancaccio's is what makes Windsor Terrace special. Top notch food whatever you get.  The chicken is superb and a relatively inexpensive family meal. The sandwiches I will miss the most. Just amazing sandwiches that make me salivate while I write this. Watching the staff prep the food while the music is blasting when you wait is part of the experience of this local neighborhood staple. But its Joe that really makes this place special. No bs guy who knows food with a great heart. I once crutched in a day before Thanksgiving with no where to go due to my injury. Joe said he was sold out of Thanksgiving food. But then managed to scratch together a bit of extras and I was magically able to buy a few plates. I was touched by the generosity. One of the nicest things someone has done for me. I wish Brancaccio's the most success. I will visit when I'm back.
Their fish sandwich is one of my favorites
I Love the sandwiches. Unbelievable flavors from the combination of ingredients Joe puts together. Try them all!
Excellent meals to go including roast chicken, meatloaf, meatballs, eggplant, roast veggies and delicious sandwiches! Menu changes daily.
This place is so over priced for a sand which $19 for a San which that took them 3 mins to make we should all make that kind of money

I've never been disappointed by anything Joe serves. The sandwiches are great (but only served until 2 I think), the meatloaf is my favorite but you can't go wrong. As far as the prepared foods I recommend the pesto, snow peas, and if he has any the eggplant parm. Best eggplant I've ever eaten, the layers are so thin it's a work of art.
Best deli counter in the 'hood. No doubt. Sandwiches or prepared foods, it's all 11/10.

Brancaccio’s is one of those places that will make you feel like a New Yorker. This small, Windsor Terrace staple serves up legendary food (including a meatball sandwich, for which they are known) in addition to some specialty groceries and I believe they also do catering. This generational eatery will not disappoint, as my partner and I regularly walk over to grab sandwiches before making another pit stop at Steeplechase next door for some coffee. This is one of my favorite places in Brooklyn, in fact I’ll be strolling over there later today for one of those sandwiches I mentioned. They sell out, so you should go there now. Although they are closed on Mondays and Tuesdays.
Amazing porchetta sandwich. Just out of this world, best I've ever had.
DELICIOUS food. One of my favorite restaurants here in the area.
Owner is extremely rude
Astonishingly good and fresh. The steak was outrageous and the meatballs were the best I’ve ever had. I’ll be going back tomorrow for more.
Very bad person.bad service.....
Great food!
Homecooking...
The food was sooo incredibly delicious a part of me wants to save the other half for my wife so she can taste this amazingness the other part is gonna finish this sandwich 🤷‍♂️🤷‍♂️  😍😍
Fantastic sandwiches and sides. Love the neighborhood and staff.
This place is a hidden gem. The food is always on point and NEVER disappoints. Anyone that doesn’t get chefs sense of humor shouldn’t even get to eat that food! You the man CHEF!
Good food to take out. I love this place and the sandwiches!!😄🥰😀
All the food is high quality and prepared well. A gem of a place,especially when you need a hearty meal and no energy to prepare it.
Joe B makes the best food, always.

I am not exaggerating when I say that Brancaccio's probably makes the best sandwiches in New York City. Aside from The Amazing food, Joe the owner is always a pleasure to see and has a great sense of humor. Make your way here, you won't regret it.
Fantastic sandwiches and pastries. Best find of my month in Brooklyn
I had the best chicken salad sandwich in my life today... Nuff sed!!
Love Joey B

This is a neighborhood treasure!  We bring in food every week and it’s always fabulous. I’m vegetarian and the choices here are amazing.  Joe is aware of my food choices and will always steer me to the meat free ones! My family loves the chicken and fish items.  The bread is awesome. You can’t go wrong. Thank you for delicious, healthy, fresh and reliable eats!
The only place where whatever they have left at the end of the day is still better than most restaurants made to order.
Excellent home made food consistently done well. Support small business

They closed 30 mins early. When I walked in they were nearly done cleaning and and said I couldn't order because they were closed. They had to have started before I walked in meaning if you get there in there last hours, it's too bad.
Best meatball sub in Brooklyn
The best
Great selection of sandwiches for any taste

This place is too good to be true. It's the local, neighbourhood sandwich place of my dreams. Great, complex fillings in perfectly crusty, sightly chewy bread. Great atmosphere and personable and helpful service. Very good value for money too! That this institution remains on a quiet, Brooklyn street shows the values upon which it is built. Great quality, community, and no pretence.
Delicious!!!
Great sandwiches!! Organic roast chickens are well worth it.
A real neighborhood jem. Great rotisserie chicken as well as Italian sandwiches.

Best take out in the area. The roast chicken is amazing, as are the artichokes, the broccolirabe and the roasted root veggies.  The sandwiches are always great with new ones added often. I haven't gotten the same one twice and I always have trouble picking one.

The rotisserie chicken infused with lemon & herbs, is ridiculously good. The chicken is perfect for when you don’t want to cook. They sell them quickly, so you need to pick them up early.  The sandwiches are fantastic as well. It can be a little pricey but worth it now and then.

The sandwiches and sides are unbelievable! Joe's a master Artist when it comes to cooking and pairing flavor profiles. Every sandwich I have tried has made my taste buds breakdance! Lol The spot is small but the flavors are huge, and if you haven't tried Brancaccio's yet you are truly missing out! This Brooklyn Gem is doing everything right!

This is by far one of the best specialty food shops in Brooklyn. There has yet to be a sandwich or side that I tried that didn’t blow me away. The detail and care for pairing these incredible ingredients is what makes Joe’s food amazing. Every time you take a bite you are amazed. If you’re looking for an adventure for your mouth and belly - come to Brancaccio’s you will never be disappointed!

This place is so Good!! The sandwiches are to die for and all the side salads are amazing. The owner Joe was a nice guy. I'll definitely be coming back soon. I heard the rotisserie chicken is ridiculous but they sell out super fast. I gotta try to get one next time.

I've been coming here for a little bit over two years. I have tried just about every sandwich on the menu and all I can say is if you have never been here, you don't know what a sandwich is!! The sides are also unbelievably delicious. Small spot, with authentic gourmet Italian ingredients, perfectly seasoned, sauteed, and or baked. The flavors are paired so well there is nothing I won't try that Joe makes. My girlfriend hates mustard and she eats a sandwich with mustard on it from Brancaccio's. The Joe is a great guy, straight to the point and no BS. His food is straight up ridiculously amazing and nothing less. Whoever gave this place a one star review is lying to themselves, the food is the best you ever had or you should stick to eating fast-food. Poor snowflakes, leave your entitled attitude at the door, don't question the artist on how he makes his art, just enjoy the art or move along. I'm salivating just thinking about a Brancaccio's sandweeeech!

Pretentious restaurateur unaware that food is art and art is to be shared, openly and graciously. Instead I was scoffed at when asking for menu details, my guest and I were given little to no detail of food choices. We walked out with a strong sense of distaste and a cold bag of subpar food. Do better..
Excellent food, prepared to our needs, fair price,

Thankfully there’s no seating otherwise the wait to get into this place would be atrocious. It’s kinda ingenious, if this was a sit down place there would be a two hour wait, prices would be much higher, yet they would take in less money because they could never match the sales/turnaround or staffing costs. Whole chicken with two large fancy sides for only $16, excellent sandwiches for only $7-9, you can’t beat that. This is the only spot I’ve ever seen in BK that serves fantastic food that isn’t way overpriced nor has some goofy gimmick they’re trying to use as an excuse for outrageous prices.

Best sandwiches in BK. Their bread is from Caputo's downtown. Everything is done in house. The music is great. Every neighborhood deserves a place like this. I've lived in the area for 5 years. I have never been disappointed here. Ever. 10 stars!
Meatball King of Brooklyn. Get the meatballs and the  artichokes.
One of my favorite places to grab lunch. The chicken cutlet special sandwich is my favorite sandwich of all time.
Owner is so nice and food was amazing! Did a catered order in less than 3 hours, plus gave me a free soda! Go here!
Best food in da hood!
A destination and a shrine.
Great sandwich, great service, great food!

Joe’s a sandwich artist that balances flavors like a composer balances voices. I’ve had half a dozen of his creations and each and everyone was a revelation. They make a hell of bird too. Boutique cuisine at bodega prices.

Wonderful food, great rotating variety. Terrific innovative sandwiches for lunch,  and expertly seasoned and prepared take-out for dinner. Barely a week goes by when we don't take advantage of Joe's delicious, convenient food once or twice.  Highly recommended.
Everything is always fresh and delicious.
Owner of place super friendly and food was amazing! Must get there before 4 next time, try one of their special sandwiches.

A hidden italian gem. It has an old world classic Brooklyn feel, like  somewhere your italian grandma dragged you to as a kid or this place could be in the set of The Godfather. Real NYers will understand and appreciate it. As far as the sandwiches I didn't get the chance to try it yet, they were sold out. (Updated The sandwiches are ridiculously delicious they are worth the wait!! Lots of choices for the sandwiches. They have unbelievably fresh ingredients, everything home-made, and the bread is the classic Italian thick crusted brooklyn bread you can't get anywhere else.) The food I had was cooked and seasoned to perfection. I can tell from the ingredients Joe the owner (nice guy) knows what he's doing for sure. The broccoli rabe & Penne was perfection. The bacon Macaroni & cheese well anything with bacon is good but the cheesiness was great , flavors mixed well and pasta cooked perfect. Ill be coming back asap for a sandwich!  Anyone in the area should check it out!
Best place to eat!
Great food, great owner and staff.

Great spot with a delicious selection of sandwiches and hot foods. Joe and his crew make the most of the small shop and deliver quality every time. Get the pot roast sandwich for those days when your looking to indulge or the BLT (there’s no lettuce, broccoli rabe instead) for a lighter but still amazing bite. The meatballs with pine nuts and raisins are a must as well. Stop by and start eating your way through his hand written menu.
I love the egg plant parmesan,  roast chicken and the pork shoulder sandwich is incredible.
The best thing that ever happened to the neighborhood and my palate
Excellent food, cuisine, preparation and service. I trust the quality of all that Joe prepares, so my biggest problem is choosing from the entire menu! AND service with a smile.
The passion for consistency and tasty food shows.  I get the roast chickens; and the sandwiches.  Eggplant parm, blt with broccoli rabe, ... forget the brunch wars, go here it's always a brunch  win,
Amazing Italian food
Everything they make is delicious. Hands down best sandwiches in the area.
A very personal and friendly Italian food shop with delicious Italian take out. The friendliness of the owner makes this place a local staple and worth going to.
Amazing sandwiches and rotisserie chickens for a great value. The chicken artichoke and pot roast sandwiches are out faves.
Brancahios has the best pasta and the best egg sandwiches on the planet
A real neighborhood staple,  perfect for supplying picnics in the park or dinner at home
Very good food especially the green eggs and ham sandwich 😋
Incredible smells the moment you walk in! Great service and fabulous food. My compliments to the chef!
Food. Service. Joe.
Wonderful
Awesome sandwiches.  Go early and get a chicken.  Great operation

Owner has a bad attitude towards high schoolers even though they're equally spending the same amount of money as us adults. I get a feeling that the staff might be underpaid and they don't really look happy. Food is good but slightly overpriced in my eyes. Alright overall. Owner should fix his attitude.

Chicken and guacamole and the chicken 'special' (chicken, prosciutto, artichoke, fontina, hot sauce) are both top notch as are the other sandwiches. The deli stuff is also all really good.  Honestly you can't go wrong with anything there.  They sometimes run out of bread, so come before 1 or 2.
Great tasting food. Only for eating out.
Good quality food to take away and nice sandwiches. Quite pricey.
These sandwiches are so delicious.

(Translated by Google) The best Italian style sandwich in New York. Super recommendation the eggplant sandwich with Parmesan.  (Original) El mejor sándwich estilo italiano de Nueva York. Super recomendación el sándwich de berenjenas a la parmesana.

Seeing as how I work across the street from this place, I decided to give it a try.  I ordered the pork shoulder sandwich and man oh man is it good.  There was ham and sweet pickles with some cheese.  Definitely reminded me of a cuban sandwich but maybe even better.  Wasn't sure what to expect but was told that the sandwiches were and pretty big.  Did not disappoint.  Sandwiches go for anywhere between $5-$9.  Will be coming back for another round of that pork shoulder sandwich.
simply the best. real dealio.

Joe and his team, mostly his team, are hard at work at Brancaccio's. You will often see the team cranking out decent sandwiches, sides, pastries, etc. for sale. You will also have a front row seat to an interesting show, one in which you can order something and then watch Joe yell at his team and sometimes even his customers. Most sandwiches go about $5-7 each and there are varying costs to many of the other items. This place does the job when you're nearby. Not necessarily worth going out your way to make the trip there, but if you're in the area, there are far worse places to go to.
Fantastic food. Reasonable prices. Friendly, clean, well-run. Very high quality in all ways. Huge asset to the neighborhood. Only wish they were open on Tuesdays!

My friend told me about this sandwich shop. I loved the meatball with raisins and fresh mozzarella cheese.  I also like the Italian tuna sandwich. The food is really good. I did not buy the chicken but it looks delicious. It was golden brown and the aroma was heavenly. I also heard the breakfast sandwiches are very good. The prices are reasonable. The staff is very friendly. i will be back.
Best sandwiches in the neighborhood!

So you think that an old school Italian deli doesn't exist in the yuppified Brooklyn, NY anymore? Well, guess again my friend. Brancaccio's made me feel like it was 1986 and I was in a FILA sweat suit on 86th street doing the strut. The stuffed tomatoes are to die for. To. Die. For. Everything they serve is A #1, so you can't go wrong but really, the tomatoes. eat one. Now.

Want the flavor of a home-cooked meal but aren't up to cooking? Walk to Brancaccio's (or drive if you have to) to get some of the best fresh Italian food in Brooklyn. Seriously. I walked in one evening, starving after a pedi, to grab dinner and walked out with spicy pasta accompanied by the most deliciously roasted tomatoes EVER. I have since been back and am glad to see that the roasted tomatoes, crusted with parmesan and stuffed with garlic are likely menu regulars. The staff is friendly and I always see the owner, who I always thank for bringing this deliciousness to Kensington. Word is that they're switching storefronts and expanding, but not to restaurant proportions. That's fine by me since I like to bring the delicious food home!

I discovered this place a little over a year ago, and have to go there almost every single week.  He makes the best roasted chicken I have ever tasted.  It is infused with lemon and thyme.  His sandwiches are also excellent.  My favorite is the trout.
